<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="125" type="taxonomic notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="125">Taxonomic notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="125">
The distribution and identity of 
<taxonomicName genus="L." lsidName="L. minutum" pageId="0" pageNumber="125" rank="species" species="minutum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="125">L. minutum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
remains in doubt. Fabricius (1798) did not specify the number of specimens examined, but a single male type is known. Moure (1960a) examined this type of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fabricius" authorityYear="1798" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Hylaeus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Hylaeus minutus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="125" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="minutus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="125">Hylaeus minutus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Fabricius and transferred it to 
<taxonomicName authority="" authorityName="Robertson" authorityYear="1902" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Dialictus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Dialictus (Chloralictus)" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="125" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Chloralictus">Dialictus (Chloralictus)</taxonomicName>
. The type locality is &quot; 
<taxonomicName family="Halictidae" genus="Americae" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Americae insulus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="125" rank="species" species="insulus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="125">Americae insulus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
&quot;, clarified subsequently to be &quot; 
<taxonomicName family="Halictidae" genus="Americae" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Americae meridionalis subsp. insulus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="125" rank="subSpecies" species="meridionalis" subSpecies="insulus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="125">Americae meridionalis insulus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
&quot; (Fabricius 1804). Moure (1960b) thought it was from St. Vincent. 
<bibRefCitation author="Moure, JS" journalOrPublisher="Smithsonian Institution Press, Washington DC" pageId="0" pageNumber="125" refId="B66" refString="Moure, JS, Hurd, PD, 1987. An annotated catalog of the halictid bees of the Western Hemisphere (Hymenoptera: Halictidae). Smithsonian Institution Press, Washington DC" title="An annotated catalog of the halictid bees of the Western Hemisphere (Hymenoptera: Halictidae)." year="1987">Moure and Hurd (1987)</bibRefCitation>
considered it a possible senior synonym of 
<taxonomicName genus="L." lsidName="L. sanctivincenti" pageId="0" pageNumber="125" rank="species" species="sanctivincenti">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="125">L. sanctivincenti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. However, 
<bibRefCitation author="Ebmer, AW" journalOrPublisher="Nachrichtenblatt der Bayerischen Entomologen" pageId="0" pageNumber="125" pagination="111 - 127" refId="B21" refString="Ebmer, AW, 1974. Von Linne bis Fabricius beschriebene westpalaearktische Arten der Genera Halictus und Lasioglossum. Nachrichtenblatt der Bayerischen Entomologen 23: 111 - 127" title="Von Linne bis Fabricius beschriebene westpalaearktische Arten der Genera Halictus und Lasioglossum." volume="23" year="1974">Ebmer (1974)</bibRefCitation>
suggests that the specimen may be from St. Thomas in the Virgin Islands, as the underside of the label read &quot;S. Thomae&quot;. The latter locality information may not be a reliable indication of the 
<normalizedToken originalValue="specimen’s">specimen's</normalizedToken>
original collection, but rather the shipping origin to Denmark (L. Vilhelmsen, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="125">pers. comm.</emphasis>
). Photographs of the specimen were examined (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 23" captionStartId="F23" captionText="Figure 23. Lasioglossum (Dialictus) minutum (Fabricius), syntype male of Hylaeus minutus Fabricius A dorsal habitus B head, oblique frontal-ventral view C lateral habitus. Images courtesy of the Natural History Museum of Denmark. Photographs by Mikkel Hoegh Post. http: // www. daim. snm. ku. dk / search-in-types" figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1089.72645.figure23" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/660588" pageId="0" pageNumber="125">23</figureCitation>
), and it seems consistent with 
<taxonomicName genus="L." lsidName="L. sanctivincenti" pageId="0" pageNumber="125" rank="species" species="sanctivincenti">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="125">L. sanctivincenti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Without certainty of its island of origin or physical examination of the holotype of 
<taxonomicName genus="L." lsidName="L. minutum" pageId="0" pageNumber="125" rank="species" species="minutum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="125">L. minutum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
a formal synonymy seems premature.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="125">
The nomenclature of 
<taxonomicName genus="L." lsidName="L. minutum" pageId="0" pageNumber="125" rank="species" species="minutum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="125">L. minutum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is somewhat confusing as discussed by earlier authors (
<bibRefCitation author="Ebmer, AW" journalOrPublisher="Nachrichtenblatt der Bayerischen Entomologen" pageId="0" pageNumber="125" pagination="111 - 127" refId="B21" refString="Ebmer, AW, 1974. Von Linne bis Fabricius beschriebene westpalaearktische Arten der Genera Halictus und Lasioglossum. Nachrichtenblatt der Bayerischen Entomologen 23: 111 - 127" title="Von Linne bis Fabricius beschriebene westpalaearktische Arten der Genera Halictus und Lasioglossum." volume="23" year="1974">Ebmer 1974</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation author="Moure, JS" journalOrPublisher="Smithsonian Institution Press, Washington DC" pageId="0" pageNumber="125" refId="B66" refString="Moure, JS, Hurd, PD, 1987. An annotated catalog of the halictid bees of the Western Hemisphere (Hymenoptera: Halictidae). Smithsonian Institution Press, Washington DC" title="An annotated catalog of the halictid bees of the Western Hemisphere (Hymenoptera: Halictidae)." year="1987">Moure and Hurd (1987)</bibRefCitation>
considered it preoccupied by Schrank (i.e., 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Apis" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Apis minuta" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="125" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="minuta">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="125">Apis minuta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Schrank 1781). However, 
<bibRefCitation author="Ebmer, AW" journalOrPublisher="Nachrichtenblatt der Bayerischen Entomologen" pageId="0" pageNumber="125" pagination="111 - 127" refId="B21" refString="Ebmer, AW, 1974. Von Linne bis Fabricius beschriebene westpalaearktische Arten der Genera Halictus und Lasioglossum. Nachrichtenblatt der Bayerischen Entomologen 23: 111 - 127" title="Von Linne bis Fabricius beschriebene westpalaearktische Arten der Genera Halictus und Lasioglossum." volume="23" year="1974">Ebmer (1974)</bibRefCitation>
considered 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Schrank’s">Schrank's</normalizedToken>
bee to be a 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fabricius" authorityYear="1793" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Hylaeus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Hylaeus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="125" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="125">Hylaeus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, although 
<bibRefCitation author="Warncke, K" journalOrPublisher="Polskie Pismo Entomologiczne" pageId="0" pageNumber="125" pagination="81 - 123" refId="B85" refString="Warncke, K, 1975. Beitraege zur systematik und Verbreitung der Furchenbienen in der Tuerkei (Hymenoptera, Apoidea, Halictus). Polskie Pismo Entomologiczne 45: 81 - 123" title="Beitraege zur systematik und Verbreitung der Furchenbienen in der Tuerkei (Hymenoptera, Apoidea, Halictus)." volume="45" year="1975">Warncke (1975)</bibRefCitation>
disagreed. Unless 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Schrank’s">Schrank's</normalizedToken>
bee can be assigned to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Curtis" authorityYear="1833" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Lasioglossum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Lasioglossum" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="125" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="125">Lasioglossum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, it cannot be considered a senior secondary homonym. Two definite cases of secondary homonymy exist, one of which has not been previously resolved. 
<bibRefCitation author="Kirby, W" journalOrPublisher="Privately published, Ipswich" pageId="0" pageNumber="125" refId="B52" refString="Kirby, W, 1802. Monographia Apum Angliae. Privately published, Ipswich" title="Monographia Apum Angliae." year="1802">Kirby (1802</bibRefCitation>
: 61-62) described 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Melitta" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Melitta minuta" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="125" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="minuta">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="125">Melitta minuta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which he attributes to Schrank. However, Kirby is typically credited with authorship (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1002/mmnd.48019210103" author="Bluethgen, P" journalOrPublisher="Deutsche entomologische Zeitschrift" pageId="0" pageNumber="125" pagination="267 - 302" refId="B7" refString="Bluethgen, P, 1921. Die deutschen Arten der Bienengattung Halictus Latr. (Hym.). Deutsche entomologische Zeitschrift 1: 267 - 302, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1002/mmnd.48019210103" title="Die deutschen Arten der Bienengattung Halictus Latr. (Hym.)." url="https://doi.org/10.1002/mmnd.48019210103" volume="1" year="1921">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Blüthgen">Bluethgen</normalizedToken>
1921
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Ebmer, AW" journalOrPublisher="Nachrichtenblatt der Bayerischen Entomologen" pageId="0" pageNumber="125" pagination="111 - 127" refId="B21" refString="Ebmer, AW, 1974. Von Linne bis Fabricius beschriebene westpalaearktische Arten der Genera Halictus und Lasioglossum. Nachrichtenblatt der Bayerischen Entomologen 23: 111 - 127" title="Von Linne bis Fabricius beschriebene westpalaearktische Arten der Genera Halictus und Lasioglossum." volume="23" year="1974">Ebmer 1974</bibRefCitation>
) since he acknowledged key differences between his bee and 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Schrank’s">Schrank's</normalizedToken>
and doubted that they were the same. 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Kirby’s">Kirby's</normalizedToken>
bee is a secondary junior homonym of 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Fabricius’s">Fabricius's</normalizedToken>
name. 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Schenck" baseAuthorityYear="1853" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Lasioglossum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Lasioglossum parvulum" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="125" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="parvulum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="125">Lasioglossum parvulum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Schenck) is now the valid name for 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Kirby’s">Kirby's</normalizedToken>
bee. More recently, 
<bibRefCitation author="Pauly, A" journalOrPublisher="Zoologische Verhandlingen" pageId="0" pageNumber="125" pagination="1 - 58" refId="B71" refString="Pauly, A, 1986. Les abeilles de la sous-famille des Halictinae en Nouvelle-Guinee et dans L'archipel Bismarck (Hymenoptera: Apoidea: Halictidae). Zoologische Verhandlingen 227: 1 - 58" title="Les abeilles de la sous-famille des Halictinae en Nouvelle-Guinee et dans L'archipel Bismarck (Hymenoptera: Apoidea: Halictidae)." volume="227" year="1986">Pauly (1986)</bibRefCitation>
described 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pauly" authorityYear="1986" class="Insecta" genus="Homalictus" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Homalictus minutus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="125" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="minutus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="125">Homalictus minutus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which is now transferred to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Curtis" authorityYear="1833" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Lasioglossum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Lasioglossum" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="125" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="125">Lasioglossum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1080/713849618" author="Danforth, BN" journalOrPublisher="&quot; Systematic Biology" pageId="0" pageNumber="125" pagination="268 - 283" refId="B18" refString="Danforth, BN, Ji, S, 2001. Australian Lasioglossum + Homalictus form a monophyletic group: resolving the &quot;Australian enigma. &quot; Systematic Biology 50: 268 - 283, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1080/713849618" title="Australian Lasioglossum + Homalictus form a monophyletic group: resolving the &quot; Australian enigma." url="https://doi.org/10.1080/713849618" volume="50" year="2001">Danforth and Ji 2001</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1016/j.ympev.2012.08.013" author="Gibbs, J" journalOrPublisher="Molecular Phylogenetics and Evolution" pageId="0" pageNumber="125" pagination="926 - 939" refId="B48" refString="Gibbs, J, Brady, SG, Kanda, K, Danforth, BN, 2012. Phylogeny of halictine bees supports a shared origin of eusociality for Halictus and Lasioglossum (Apoidea: Anthophila: Halictidae). Molecular Phylogenetics and Evolution 65: 926 - 939, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1016/j.ympev.2012.08.013" title="Phylogeny of halictine bees supports a shared origin of eusociality for Halictus and Lasioglossum (Apoidea: Anthophila: Halictidae)." url="https://doi.org/10.1016/j.ympev.2012.08.013" volume="65" year="2012">Gibbs et al. 2012</bibRefCitation>
; 
